The letter '''aliph''' (sometimes also Latinised '''aleph''' or '''alif''') is the first letter in the [[Urdu]] alphabet. The sound of the letter is that of an a or u in the English language especially as used in the words <u>a</u>rt or <u>u</u>mbrella. The voice is usually dependant on the context this letter is used in. For Urdu, this letter was borrowed from the Arabic language where also is serves as the first letter in the alphabet.

